The paper deals with mechanism design and game theory, which are central topics in cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) and cs.EC (Emerging Technologies in Computational Social Choice). The use of limited knowledge and uncertainty in valuations suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the focus on single-parameter domains suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which often deals with optimization problems in one-dimensional spaces.
